  <discussion>This treatment follows M. T. Gallego et al. (2006) in including Syntrichia pagorum with forms of S. laevipila reported in the literature from North America, but this is tentative pending a careful reexamination of this complex of small, corticolous plants.  These plants might be confused superfically with S. papillosa, but the leaf margins are plane, the abaxial surface of the costa is smooth and shiny, the propagula are leaf-like, and the leaf cells are pluripapillose in S. laevipila.  The other taxa with leaf-like propagula, S. chisosa and S. ammonsiana, are never corticolous.</discussion>
